arch:property.oc:show_val: The floor is comprised of smoothed sandstone flagstones, set into dirt, with 35 rows of pavers set between the south wall of the trench (Locus 12) and the remaining unexcavated soil section.
Dimensions: 17.87 m north south (on the west side) and 18.37 m north-south (on the east side)-by-4.20 m east west.

Phase IV: Nabataean Grand Design: 1st c. BCE to CE 1st c. The full Lower Temenos is constructed, complete with additional subterranean channels and drains, the Hexagonal Pavement, the East and West Triple Colonnades and Cryptoportici, the East and West Exedrae and the Lower Temenos Retaining Wall. East west crosswall is built in the West Cryptoporticus ca. 20 m north of the West Exedra.
Opening Elevation: South  892.986 m; Middle  892.821 m; North  892.766 m.
